'''Yin Water Rabbit''', also known as '''Kibō''' (癸卯, Mizunotō, Kisui no Usagi, Kisui no U, Kibō), is one of the elements in the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支}}.
It is the 40th combination in the Sexagenary cycle, following {{ill|Ren Yin|ja|壬寅}} and preceding {{ill|Jia Chen|ja|甲辰}}. According to {{ill|Yin-Yang and the Five Elements|ja|陰陽五行思想}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stem|ja|十干}} {{ill|Gui|ja|癸}} corresponds to Yin {{ill|Water (Wu Xing)|ja|水}}, while the {{ill|Earthly Branch|ja|十二支}} {{ill|Mao|ja|卯}} corresponds to Yin {{ill|Wood (Wu Xing)|ja|木}}, creating a {{ill|Five Elements#Mutual generation|ja|相生}} (Water generates Wood) relationship.
